            <p>
              Losing hair is part of a natural process of hair growth and replacement. Hair follicles go through the growth and resting cycle in a non-synchronized way. Genetics is the most common cause of hair loss among both, men and women. In fact, heredity accounts for 95% of all the cases of alopecia (baldness). The remaining 5% of the cases can depend on a number other factors like diet, stress, illness, medications and more.
            </p>
       <div class="tag-box tag-box-v2 box-shadow shadow-effect-1">
